===Etymology===
From ancient Greek [[τραγωδία]] (''tragodia'') "epic play, tragedy", from [[τράγος]] (''tragos'') "goat" + [[ωδή]] (''ode'') "song", a reference to the goat-satyrs of the theatrical plays of the [[Dorians]].

===Noun===
'''tragedy''' (''plural'' tragedies)
#A [[drama]] or similar work, in which the main [[character]] is brought to [[ruin]] or otherwise suffers the [[extreme]] [[consequence]]s of some [[tragic]] [[flaw]] or [[weakness]] of character.
#The [[genre]] of such works, and the [[art]] of producing them.
#A [[disastrous]] [[event]], especially one involving great [[loss]] of [[life]] or [[injury]]

